   psql -c "EXPLAIN SELECT COUNT(*) FROM public.passenger WHERE sex = 'male';"

messages.content:
Now I can see all the medals. Let me check which ones were won in the mid-twenties (ages 24-26, years 2011-2013). Looking at the data, none of the medals were won in those years. Let me double-check by looking at the years: all medals were won in 2015-2019, which would be ages 28-32.

Wait, let me recalculate: if Laura was born in 1987:
- Age 24: 2011 (born July 22, 1987 + 24 years)
- Age 25: 2012
- Age 26: 2013

None of the medals are in this range. Let me write a proper SQL query to verify:

function.arguments:
{"command": "cat <<'EOF' > /tmp/query.sql
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM medal m
JOIN format f ON m.format_id = f.format_id
JOIN tournament t ON f.tournament_id = t.tournament_id
JOIN athlete a ON t.athlete_id = a.athlete_id
JOIN personalinformation p ON a.athlete_id = p.athlete_id
WHERE a.name = 'Laura Graves'
  AND m.year >= p.birth_year + 24
  AND m.year <= p.birth_year + 26;
EOF
cat /tmp/query.sql"}
